# average duration by zipcode/race
tab <- san %>% 
  group_by(zip, race_eth) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(av.duration = round(mean(duration, na.rm = T), 1), sd.duration = round(sd(duration, na.rm = T), 1))

load("~/GitHub/san/sa_survey.RData")

san %>% 
  filter(health != "NA") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = race_eth, fill = health)) +
  geom_bar() +
  geom_text(aes(label = ..count..), stat = "count", position=position_stack(0.5), vjust = 0, size = 2) +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(option = "E", begin = .2, end = .8) +
  facet_grid(~zip) +
  ggtitle("Responses by zip code and mental health status", 
          subtitle = "How often have you been bothered by the feeling nervous, anxious, or on edge") +
  xlab(NULL) + 
  theme_light() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, size = 9))

  ggplot() +

san <- san %>% 
  mutate(rep_email = if_else(email == lag(email, n = 1, order_by = email), "rep_email", "first_entry"))

san_re <- san %>% 
  mutate(rep_email = if_else(email == lag(email, n = 1, order_by = email), "rep_email", "first_entry")) %>% 
  filter(email %in% rep_emails) %>% 
  arrange(email)

save(san, file = "~/GitHub/san/sa_survey.RData")
save(san_re, file = "~/GitHub/san/sa_survey_rep_emails.RData")
write.csv(x = rep_emails, file = "~/GitHub/san/repeated_emails.csv")
poorh <- san %>% 
  mutate(ageg = case_when(age %in% min(age):29 ~ "20-29",
                          age %in% 30:39 ~ "30-39",
                          age %in% 40:49 ~ "40-49",
                          age %in% 50:59 ~ "50-59",
                          age %in% 60:max(age) ~ "60+")) %>% 
  group_by(race_eth, zip, gender) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(poorh = round(mean(as.numeric(days_poor_health), na.rm = T),1)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  select(race_eth, zip, gender, poorh) %>% 
  glimpse()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'race_eth', 'zip'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
## Rows: 28
## Columns: 4
## $ race_eth <ord> NH-White, NH-White, NH-White, NH-White, NH-White, NH-Black, N~
## $ zip      <chr> "Elm Creek", "Elm Creek", "Jefferson Heights", "Jefferson Hei~
## $ gender   <chr> "Female", "Male", "Female", "Male", "Other", "Female", "Male"~
## $ poorh    <dbl> 3.6, 2.7, 3.3, 2.5, 12.0, 2.4, 1.5, 2.4, 3.1, 3.0, 5.8, 0.0, ~
poorh %>% 
  filter(gender != "Other", race_eth!= "NH-Other") %>% 
  mutate(label = poorh) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = poorh, y = race_eth)) +
  geom_line(color = "gray50", size = 1) +
  geom_point(aes(fill = as.factor(gender), color = as.factor(gender)), size = 4, shape = 19) +
  facet_grid(~zip) +
  geom_text(aes(label = label, x = poorh), nudge_y = 0.25, size = 3.2) +
  geom_text(aes(label = gender, x = poorh), nudge_y = -0.25, size = 3.2) +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(option = "B", begin = .2, end = .8, direction = 1) +
  scale_color_viridis_d(option = "B", begin = .2, end = .8, direction = 1) +
  labs(title = "Days of poor health | Women and Men",
    subtitle = "January 2021",
    x = "Average number of days with poor physical or mental health",
    y = "Days with poor healht", 
    caption = "Source: San Antonio Energy and Time Use Survey") +
  theme_light() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12), plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 11), 
        legend.position = "none", legend.title = element_blank(), 
        axis.title = element_text(size = 10), 
        axis.text = element_text(size = 10), 
        axis.text.y = element_text(size =10, face = "bold"),
        plot.title.position = "plot", 
        plot.caption = element_text(size = 8), 
        strip.background = element_rect(color = "gray20", linetype = "solid"), 
        strip.text = element_text(color = "black", size = 8))
